nxpac.label.description.download-log: Download Nuxeo server.log. Returns a zip.
nxpac.label.description.download-conf: Download all configuration parameters. Output is similar to 'nuxeoctl showconf'. Returns a zip.
nxpac.label.description.distribution: Display information about the Nuxeo Server instance (version, environment, bundles, etc.) Uses Automation to fetch env values and the 'management' endpoint to get distribution information.
nxpac.label.description.orphaned-binarie: Delete binaries not linked to any document. This action frees storage space.
nxpac.label.description.probes: Display information from the Probes endpoint.
nxpac.label.description.recompute-views: Generate picture renditions. Can be used to force-regenerate them as well.
nxpac.label.description.recompute-thumbn: Generate document thumbnails. Can be used to force-regenerate them as well.
nxpac.label.description.recompute-videos: Generate video renditions or video info. Can be used to force-regenerate them as well.
nxpac.label.description.reindex-reposito: Reindex the whole repository. Tip: use Nuxeo Dev Tools to limit this to certain documents.
nxpac.label.description.page-providers: Display information about deployed Page Providers.
nxpac.label.description.gc-orphaned-vers: Delete any document versions for which the live document no longer exists.
nxpac.label.description.gc-workflows: Delete any workflows for which: all documents have been deleted; the state is 'done'; or the state is 'cancelled'.
nxpac.label.description.stream-scale: Display info about streams and auto-scaling options.
